data.name: Lobster Tail with Garlic Butter
data.quickTastyDescription: Succulent lobster tails drenched in rich garlic butter, perfect for a special occasion or a delightful treat at home.
detailedCookingInstructions: Using kitchen scissors, carefully cut the top shell of the lobster tails down the middle, exposing the meat.
In a small saucepan, melt the butter over medium heat and add the minced garlic.
Cook the garlic in the butter until fragrant (about 1-2 minutes), being careful not to burn it.
Stir in lemon juice, salt, and pepper to the garlic butter mixture.
Place the lobster tails on a baking sheet and brush the garlic butter generously over the exposed lobster meat.
Bake in the preheated oven for about 12-15 minutes or until the lobster meat is opaque and cooked through.
Remove from the oven and drizzle more garlic butter on top if desired, then garnish with chopped parsley before serving.
data.detailedName: Baked Lobster Tail with Garlic Butter
